HEADWORD: Lucre
<hw>Lu"cre</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>lucre</ets>,
L. <ets>lucrum</ets>.]</ety> <def>Gain in money or goods; profit;
riches; -- often in an ill sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The lust of <qex>lucre</qex> and the dread of death.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lucriferous</ent>⟦br⟧
